                 <!-- note on edition: 1. ḥ > h, 2 paten (·) are deleted, 3. ṁ > ṅ, 4. ṁṅ > ṅ -->
	<p><pb n="A1v"/>ndah nihan varahakna saṅ sadu, 
<app><lem wit="#A">de</lem><rdg wit="#B">den</rdg></app> saṅ mamet hayu, 
hana ta 
<!--<app><lem type="conj" resp="#SD">saṅ h</lem><note>Mss. AB are damaged in this part</note></app>yaṅ -->
<app><lem type="conj" resp="#SD">saṅ hyaṅ</lem><rdg wit="A"><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="chars"/><seg type="component" subtype="body"><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="component"/></seg>yaṁ</rdg><rdg wit="#B">TOBEFILLEDIN</rdg></app>
siksa kandaṅ karəsian ṅaranya, 
kayatnakna voṅ sakabeh, ujar saṅ sadu, ṅagəlarkәn saṅ hyaṅ siksa kandaṅ karәsian,</p>
                <p>ini saṅ hyaṅ dasa-krәta, kundaṅən uraṅ <app><lem type="norm">rea</lem><rdg wit="#A #B">rye</rdg></app><!-- maybe just edit rea, no app entry needed -->, 
<app><lem>asiṅ nu dek</lem><rdg wit="#A"><unclear>Asiṁ nu dek·</unclear></rdg><rdg type="lacune" wit="#B"/></app> <app><lem type="emend">nañjərkən</lem><rdg wit="#A">najərkən</rdg><rdg wit="#B"><gap reason="lost"/></rdg></app><!-- convert to <rdg type="lacune" wit="#B"/>? --><!-- Is there a way to represent this kind of normalization without recourse to <app>? what about na<supplied reason="nonstandard">ñ</supplied>jərkən? or na<app><lem type="norm">ñ</lem><rdg wit="A"/><rdg type="lacuna" wit="B"/></app>jərkən  -->
 saṅ hyaṅ sasana krəta, 
pakənən hәbәl hirup həbəl <app><lem type="emend">ñovana</lem><rdg wit="#A #B">ñavana</rdg></app>, 
<app><lem type="norm">jadian</lem><rdg wit="#A">jadyan</rdg><rdg wit="#B"><gap reason="lost"/></rdg></app><!-- again, a case that does not deserve an <app> entry, I think. and why not simply keep jadyan as spelling? --> kuras <app><lem type="emend">jadian</lem><rdg wit="#A">jadya</rdg></app><!-- or spelling jadyan? is jadya[n] tahun the same phenomenon as ṅa[ñ]jĕrkĕn? --> tahun dәgdәg tajәr <app><lem type="emend">jaya</lem><rdg wit="#A">ya</rdg><rdg wit="#B"><gap reason="lost"/></rdg><!-- or other manner of encoding lacuna --></app> praṅ, 
ñovana na <app><lem wit="#B">uraṅ</lem><rdg wit="#A"><unclear>U</unclear>raṁ</rdg></app> <app><lem type="norm">rea</lem><rdg wit="#A #B">rye</rdg></app><!-- maybe no <app> needed for rea -->,</p>
                <p><app><lem wit="#B">ini</lem><rdg wit="#A"><gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="1"/>ni</rdg></app> <app><lem wit="#A">byaktana</lem><rdg wit="#B">byitana</rdg></app> saṅ hyaṅ <app><lem wit="A">dasakrәta</lem><rdg wit="#B">dasakrata</rdg></app> ṅaranya, kalaṅkaṅ saṅ hyaṅ dasa-<app><lem wit="#A">sila</lem><rdg wit="#B"><gap reason="lost" unit="chars" quantity="50000"/></rdg><note>From this passage Ms. B is missing until the word ... in <ref>...</ref><!-- Adit: How make a reference and number of </p> elements? -->, the reason why I do not indicate ms. B readings.</note></app><!-- Axelle: how to encode such a situation? -->, maya-maya saṅ hyaṅ dasa-marga, kaprәtyaksaan na dasa-indriya, pakәn ṅrәtakәn <app><lem wit="#A">di</lem><rdg source="Atja+Danasasmita1981_01"/></app> bumi<!-- bumi</lem><rdg source="Atja+Danasasmita1981_01">bumi</rdg></app>--> lamba, di bumi <app><lem type="emend">parәk</lem><rdg wit="#A">paR̥<unclear>ka</unclear></rdg></app>,</p> 
                <p>ini pakәn uraṅ ṅrәtakәn bumi  
<app><lem>lamba, caaṅ jalan</lem><rdg source="Atja+Danasasmita1981_01">lamba caaṅ jalan</rdg><rdg wit="#A">la<unclear>mbha</unclear><gap reason="lost" unit="character" quantity="3"/>ṁ<unclear>ja</unclear>lan·</rdg>
</app> 
pañjaṅ tajur, paka pradana, liñih pipir <app><lem type="emend" source="Atja+Danasasmita1981_01">caaṅ</lem><rdg wit="#A"><unclear>ca</unclear>A</rdg></app> bu<pb n="A2r"/>ruan,</p>
                

